[Event]
ControlReady
[EventDescription]
Fired when WebView2 is fully initialized and ready for use.
[Event]
ErrorOccurred
[EventDescription]
Fired when an error occurs.
[Parameter1]
errorMessage
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
Description of the error
[Event]
NavigationCompleted
[EventDescription]
Fired when navigation completes.
[Parameter1]
url
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
The URL that was navigated to
[Parameter2]
success
[Parameter2Type]
BYTE
[Parameter2Description]
Whether navigation succeeded
[Event]
NavigationStarting
[EventDescription]
Fired when navigation starts.
[Parameter1]
url
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
The URL being navigated to
[Event]
DocumentLoaded
[EventDescription]
Fired when a PDF document is loaded and fully rendered. All page elements exist â€” safe to call ImportAnnotationsData() immediately. Read PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'LoadType'} to determine how the document was loaded: 'base64', 'file', or 'url'. IMPORTANT: Guard ImportAnnotationsData() with LoadType â€” only restore annotations when LoadType = 'base64', otherwise annotations from a previous load will bleed into the new document.
[Parameter1]
pageCount
[Parameter1Type]
LONG
[Parameter1Description]
Total number of pages in the document
[Parameter2]
title
[Parameter2Type]
STRING
[Parameter2Description]
Document title (if available)
[Event]
PageChanged
[EventDescription]
Fired when the current page changes.
[Parameter1]
pageNumber
[Parameter1Type]
LONG
[Parameter1Description]
The new current page number (1-based)
[Event]
ZoomChanged
[EventDescription]
Fired when the zoom level changes.
[Parameter1]
zoomLevel
[Parameter1Type]
REAL
[Parameter1Description]
The new zoom level (1.0 = 100%)
[Event]
SearchCompleted
[EventDescription]
Fired when a search completes.
[Parameter1]
matchCount
[Parameter1Type]
LONG
[Parameter1Description]
Number of matches found
[Parameter2]
currentMatch
[Parameter2Type]
LONG
[Parameter2Description]
Current match index (1-based)
[Event]
AnnotationAdded
[EventDescription]
Fired when an annotation is added.
[Parameter1]
annotationType
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
Type of annotation (highlight, note, drawing)
[Parameter2]
pageNumber
[Parameter2Type]
LONG
[Parameter2Description]
Page where annotation was added
[Event]
AnnotationSelected
[EventDescription]
Fired when an annotation is selected.
[Parameter1]
annotationId
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
ID of the selected annotation
[Parameter2]
annotationType
[Parameter2Type]
STRING
[Parameter2Description]
Type of annotation
[Event]
BookmarkClicked
[EventDescription]
Fired when a bookmark/outline item is clicked.
[Parameter1]
title
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
Title of the bookmark
[Parameter2]
pageNumber
[Parameter2Type]
LONG
[Parameter2Description]
Destination page number
[Event]
ThumbnailClicked
[EventDescription]
Fired when a thumbnail is clicked.
[Parameter1]
pageNumber
[Parameter1Type]
LONG
[Parameter1Description]
Page number of the clicked thumbnail
[Event]
TextSelected
[EventDescription]
Fired when text is selected in the PDF.
[Parameter1]
selectedText
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
The selected text
[Parameter2]
pageNumber
[Parameter2Type]
LONG
[Parameter2Description]
Page where text was selected
[Event]
LinkClicked
[EventDescription]
Fired when a link in the PDF is clicked.
[Parameter1]
url
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
The URL of the link
[Parameter2]
isInternal
[Parameter2Type]
BYTE
[Parameter2Description]
True if link is internal to the document
[Event]
PrintCompleted
[EventDescription]
Fired when print operation completes.
[Parameter1]
success
[Parameter1Type]
BYTE
[Parameter1Description]
Whether print was successful
[Event]
ViewerReady
[EventDescription]
Fired when the PDF viewer JavaScript component is fully initialized and ready to load documents. Use this event instead of ControlReady to call LoadFile, LoadUrl, or LoadBase64.
[Event]
SaveAsBase64Ready
[EventDescription]
Fired when SaveAsBase64() completes. Contains the annotated PDF as Base64-encoded data. Pass Parm1 to a StringTheory object (e.g., st.SetValue(PDFViewerCOM.Parm1.GetValue())).
[Parameter1]
base64Data
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
Base64-encoded PDF bytes including all annotations
[Event]
AnnotationsExported
[EventDescription]
Fired when ExportAnnotations() completes. Contains the full annotation JSON including highlights, notes, and drawing strokes. Read with: PDFViewerCOM.Parm1.GetValue() Store alongside the original PDF (via SourceBase64) to enable editable round-trips.
[Parameter1]
annotationsJson
[Parameter1Type]
STRING
[Parameter1Description]
JSON string with { annotations, drawingHistory }
